text: Ina Ananieva () is a former Bulgarian gymnast and rhythmic gymnastics coach. == Biography== In 1991, Ananieva won a silver medal as part of the Bulgarian team at the World Championships in Athens, Greece. In 2012, she was appointed as head coach of the Bulgarian rhythmic gymnasts. In 2014, Ananieva became the coach of the year in Bulgarian sports after the Bulgarian women won gold in the group all-around at the 2014 World Championships. ==References== ==External links== Category:1977 births Category:Living people Category:Bulgarian rhythmic gymnasts Category:Place of birth missing (living people)
